{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}} {{Use British English|date=November 2017}} {{Infobox Journal | title = Studies in World Christianity | cover = Studies in World Christianity cover.png | discipline = [[Religious Studies]] | website = http://www.eupjournals.com/journal/swc | link1 = | link1-name = | publisher = [[Edinburgh University Press]] | country = Scotland | abbreviation = | history = 1995-present | frequency = Triannually | ISSN = 1354-9901 | eISSN = 1750-0230 | Jstor = | OCLC = 52322269 | LCCN = }} '''''Studies in World Christianity''''' is a peer-reviewed [[academic journal]] which examines the development of [[Christianity]] worldwide – known broadly as [[World Christianity]]. Its primary interests are in the rich diversity of Christianity in Africa, Asia, Latin America, Oceania, and eastern Europe, as well as diasporic forms of non-Western Christianity emerging in contexts such as Western Europe and North America. Articles in the journal engage a variety of academic disciplines – historical, theological, and social scientific.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |url= http://www.euppublishing.com/journal/swc|title= Studies in World Christianity |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website= Edinburgh University Press |access-date=7 August 2015}} </ref>
The journal is published three times a year in April, August and December by [[Edinburgh University Press]]. It is associated with the [[Centre for the Study of World Christianity]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cswc.div.ed.ac.uk/journal/ |title= Journal |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Centre for the Study of World Christianity |access-date= 7 August 2015}}</ref> formerly the Centre for the Study of Non-Western Christianity, in the [[New College, Edinburgh|School of Divinity]] at the [[University of Edinburgh]]. The journal was founded by [[Andrew F. Walls]] in April 1995 as ''Studies in World Christianity: The Edinburgh Review of Theology and Religion''.<ref>{{cite book |last=Stanley |first=Brian |editor-last1=Burrows |editor-first1=William R.|editor-last2=Gornik |editor-first2=Mark R. |editor-last3=McLean |editor-first3=Janice A.|title=Understanding World Christianity: The Vision and Work of Andrew F. Walls |publisher=Orbis Books |date=2011 |pages=57 |chapter=Chapter 5: Founding the Centre for the Study of Christianity in the Non-Western World|lastauthoramp=y}}</ref> The journal is currently edited by [[Brian Stanley (historian)|Brian Stanley]].<ref name=":0" />
