{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Thiru Eadu Vasippu''' is the festival celebrated in the worship centers of [[Ayyavazhi]]. It is celebrated for three, five, seven, ten or seventeen days annually. During these days the holy scripture of Ayyavazhi, the [[Akilattirattu Ammanai]] is sung. In [[Swamithoppepathi]] the headquarters of Ayyavazhi, it starts on the third Friday in the Tamil month of [[Tamil calendar|Kathikai]] (falls approximately in the first week of December) and continues for seventeen days and ends on the first Sunday of the Tamil month of [[Tamil calendar|Margazhi]]. 

